Durban - A man was killed when his car collided with a steel sign stanchion on the M19 near the N2 interchange on Wednesday morning.Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said that paramedics responded to the scene and found carnage. &ldquo;A single vehicle had left the roadway and collided with a steel structure leaving a man in his twenties entrapped in the wreckage. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had unfortunately passed away before their arrival,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;The man was declared deceased on the scene. The engine was found some distance from the wreckage,&rdquo; Jamieson said. He said the cause of the collision is unknown.Man killed in collision into a steel structure on the M19 Durban bound https://t.co/gItgg0EslS @rescuecare pic.twitter.com/Ec1pDAWuef24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.